rds, and host plants for butterflies round out The California Wildlife Habitat Garden, making it an indispensable primer for those about to embark on creating their own biologically diverse, environmentally friendly garden.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aGardening to attract birds -- California. 0aGardening to attract birdszCalifornia. 0aGardening to attract wildlife -- California. 0aGardening to attract wildlifezCalifornia. 7aNATURE / Plants / General.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  aamerican gardening.  abooks about wildlife.  abooks for animal lovers.  acaring for wild life.  acoffee table books.  acreating your own ecosystem.  aenvironmental ecosystems.  afixing your garden.  agardening and horticulture landscape.  agardening for dummies.  ahome school science books.  ahow to garden.  aideas for quarantine.  aliving ecosystems.  aplants and wildlife.  aprotecting wildlife.  athings to do when youre bored.  atransform backyard.  awest region gardening.  awhat seeds should i plant.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095350540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953505423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953505/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles